review_blob: 355ml bottle. Clear orange body, medium white head with good retention, lots of lacing. Aroma of peaches, grapefruit, apricots, fresh herbal peppery notes. Taste of honey, apricot jam, grapefruit zest, a touch of pine. Lovely, but a tad too sweet.

341ml bottle. Light brown clear body, medium beige head, average retention, poor amount of lacing. Aroma of dark coffee, ash, burned sugar, hints of leather. Taste is disappointingly flat: coffee, sparkling water, metallic tones, burned sugar, Splenda. I think I should stop wasting my time with Multi-Brasses.

330ml bottle. Cloudy yellow-white body, medium white head, average retention, no lacing. Aroma of yeast, watercress, banana, wheat, spices (mostly peppercorn). Taste of yeast, banana and wheat, a touch of lemon sourness. Light, effervescent. Interesting.

341ml bottle. Clear dark cola body, small mocha head with average retention and almost no lacing. Aroma of roasted malts, balsamic vinegar, leather, licorice, dark chocolate, cocoa. Smooth and round taste: dark chocolate, oak, leather, well done toast, clear hop presence. Finally a porter that doesnt taste like a stout. Very very nice.

750ml bottle. Dark brown, opaque body, medium chocolate head with good retention, nice looking lacing. Aroma of milk chocolate, peppermint, coffee, herbs, cocoa liquor. Taste of well-done toast, dark chocolate, milk shake, vanilla, light hops, peppermint. Very nice and refreshing.

341ml bottle. Clear copper body, medium beige head with decent retention, some lacing. Aroma is a bit dusty: caramel, orange candies, bread, dried apricot. Taste of caramel, grapefruit zest, candies, a hint of resins. Ok.
beer_name: Simple Malt Cascade India Pale Ale

review_blob: 341ml bottle. Clear dark amber-brown body, small beige head with average to poor retention, almost no lacing. Aroma of berries liquor, leather, caramel, barberries. Taste of candy sugar, berries, barberries, salted caramel. Not bad.

330ml bottle. Clear dark brown body, medium chocolate head with good retention and decent amount of lacing. Aroma licorice, toasted malts, burned sugar, hints of leather and some hops. Taste of dark chocolate, well done toast, leather, herbs, burned caramel. Very nice.
473ml can. Hazy golden body, big white soapy head with poor retention. aroma of grapefruit zest, wheat, banana, a touch of pine. Taste of pink grapefruit, pine, mango, peaches. A hoppy wheat? Good.

341ml bottle. Clear dark amber body, small beige head with average retention, almost no lacing. Aroma of caramel malt, black currant jam, herb liquor, a touch of leather and some metallic tones. Light tone with a strong mineral note: caramel, dried dark berries, toasted malt. Not the best interpretation of the style.

330ml bottle. Hazy yellow body, huge white head with good retention. Surprisingly fresh and floral aroma: grass, yeast, green grapes, camomile. Taste of yeast, sugar, herbs, peppercorn, leather. Very well done.

500ml bottle. Clear golden body, medium white head, average retention, poor amount of lacing. Delicious aroma: pineapple, apricot, orange marmalade, pine. Taste of grapefruit zest, oranges, peach compote, moderate amount of pine. Long aftertaste. Very nice!

500ml can. Clear pale yellow body, medium white head with decent retention, poor lacing. Aroma of grains, wet cardboard, metallic notes, some herbs. Taste of grains, sugar, corn, again metallic notes. Ok.

500ml can. Cloudy dirty copper body, medium beige head with average to poor retention, no lacing. Aroma of yeast, dough, raspberries. Taste of yeast, raspberries, wheat, some bananas. Interesting approach.
473ml can. Clear amber body, medium white head with good retention and plenty of lacing. Aroma of caramel malt, herbs, candied apples. Malty taste, plenty of herbs, caramel, apple pie. Good.

650ml bottle. Clear golden body, medium white head with good retention, lots of lacing. Aroma orange candies, pine needles, acacia honey. Taste of honey, tons of malt, pine, grapefruit zest. Oily. Very nice.

341ml bottle. Visually appealing beer. Dark cola body, small tan head with average retention. Intense aroma of roasted nuts, roasted malt, smoked prunes, chocolate. Equally satisfying taste: well done toast, smoked prunes, dried berries, roasted nuts. Very interesting, lots of flavor for the style.

473ml can. Clear amber body, medium white head average retention, poor lacing. Fresh nose of pine, caramel, grapefruit, oranges. Taste of malts, pine, grapefruit, orange, peppercorn and touch of menthol. Ok.
beer_name: Bicycle Craft Velocipede India Pale Ale

review_blob: 473ml can. Clear copper body, small beige head with average retention, lots of lacing. Aroma of peppercorn, caramel, malt, leaves and mild hoppy presence. Taste candy sugar, caramel malts, herbs, decent amount of hops. Hearty well done bitter.

473ml can. Clear dark brown body, small tan head with poor retention and no lacing. Aroma of roasted malts, licorice, blackberry jam, some metal notes. Watery taste: caramel, burned toast, ash, some chocolate. Meh.

473ml can. Clear golden body, medium white head with decent retention, lots of lacing. Aroma of honey, grains, yellow plum, a touch of citrus. Taste of honey, grains, significant amount of herbal hops for the style, spices. Ok.

473ml can. Clear dark cola body, medium mocha head with head with good retention and lots of lacing. Aroma of roasted malts, blackberry jam, leaves, hints of leather and some hops. Taste of burned toast, caramel, wood charcoal, pine. Well done.

500ml can (so unusual for Canada), beautiful artwork. Clear golden body, small white head with poor retention. Aroma of grains, mineral water and a pleasant citrus hint. Taste of grains, grassy hops, peppercorn, lemons. Interesting approach.

341ml bottle. Opaque dirty orange body, huge beige head with good retention, lots of lacing. Pleasant herbal-fruity aroma: leather, carrots, raisins, woodsy, booze. If the alcohol was a little less prominent, it wouldve been much better. Taste of caramel, herbs, buckwheat, carrots, oak, vanilla and lots of booze. Good warming effect. A bit ruff.

330ml bottle. Clear yellow body, big fluffy snow-white head with average retention, but plenty of lacing. Aroma of herbs and yeast, peppercorn, sugar and mineral water. Taste of grains, yeast, spices, herbs and some alcohol towards the end. Solid.

341ml bottle. Clear mahogany body, medium creme brulee head with average retention. Aroma of caramel, sour cherries, cloves and coriander. Taste of banana, caramel malt, sour cherries, cacao. Interesting.
beer_name: Brasseurs du Monde Gamme Grand Connaisseur LOcculte

review_blob: 473ml can. Clear dark cola body, medium brown head with good retention. Aroma of grassy hops, caramel malt, chocolate, molasses, salted caramel. Taste of dark fruits, well done toast, a touch of ash and leather, very decent amount of hops for the style. Very enjoyable.

500ml bottle. Clear dark cola body, medium mocha head with average retention, some lacing. Aroma of roasted malt, sauerkraut, herbs and hints of coffee. Taste of roasted malts, coffee, burned caramel, a touch of herbs. Dry and a bit too carbonated for my liking.

473ml can. Clear amber body, medium beige head with average retention and some lacing. Aroma of vanilla, caramel, condensed milk, Baileys. Taste is consistent with the aroma: caramel, condensed milk, vanilla. Some medicinal-metallic aftertaste. Disappointing.

341ml bottle. Clear dark amber body, small beige head with poor retention, no lacing. Aroma of sugar, alcohol, licorice, spices, dried fruit. Taste of tons of caramel, alcohol, herbs, some metallic tones and a touch of leather. Medicinal.

330ml bottle. Clear black tea body, medium beige head with minimal retention and no lacing. Aroma of raisins, yeast, leaves, caramel. Taste of yeast, dough, caramel. A tad metallic and strongly carbonated. Ok.

341ml bottle. Clear copper body, medium white head with average retention, no lacing. Aroma of candied pears, honey, spices, fruits in alcohol. Taste of caramel, lots of it, yeast, honey, a touch of spices, alcohol. Interesting.

473ml can. Slightly hazy copper body, medium white head, average retention, some lacing. Fruity aroma: peaches, mangoes, apricots, honey. Taste of grapefruit zest, caramel candies, a touch of herbs and peppercorn. Decent.

341ml bottle. Dark chocolate head, small light brown head with average to poor retention. Intense and light aroma of smoked prunes, peat, leather, molasses, black currant jam, good tobacco. Taste of hot smoked prunes, burned caramel, leather and a touch of ash. Oily and a tad flat. Sweet but still great.

500ml bottle. Clear cola body, medium latte head with average retention, some lacing. Aroma of ash, herbs, burned caramel, a bit dusty. Taste of burned toast, burned caramel, lemongrass, touch of chocolate. Light.

355ml bottle. Dark brown, almost black body, medium chocolate head with good retention, some lacing. Aroma of coffee, licorice, vanilla, dark chocolate, condensed milk, herbs. Taste of burned toast, coffee, dark chocolate, noticeable amount of hops. Really good.
beer_name: Nickel Brook Bolshevik Bastard Imperial Stout

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: 750ml bottle. Clear dark amber body, small white head with poor retention, no lacing. Heavy aroma of yeast, sour cherry, red wine, oak, old hops, leaves. Taste of sour cherries, yeast, spices, honey, vinegar. Oily and flat. Heavy stuff.
beer_name: Schneider Weisse Tap X Mein Cuve Barrique

review_blob: 355ml can. Clear pale yellow body, medium white head with decent retention. Aroma of boiled eggs, cooked vegetables, corn, cheese. Taste of grains, corn syrup, cheap cheese. Metallic aftertaste. Awful!

355ml bottle. Hazy dirty amber body, small white head, decent retention and nice amount of lacing. Aroma of tomato juice, grains, honey, herbs. Taste of grains, sugar, a bit of bread, metallic herbal hops. Very decent for the style.

330ml bottle. Clear dark copper body, medium beige head, medium retention, no lacing. Strongly yeasty aroma: dough, caramel, raisins, figs. Taste of raisins, sour cherries, yeast, plums, mildly spicy. Intense carbonation. Very good.

473ml can. Black opaque body, medium chocolate head with good retention and plenty of lacing. Aroma of grassy hops, burned toast, licorice, light coffee, cocoa. Taste of burned coffee, leather, burned sugar, ash, herbs. Lovely brew.
beer_name: Sawdust City Long, Dark Voyage to Uranus

review_blob: 500ml bottle. Clear golden-amber body, big white head with average retention, some lacing. Aroma of citrus zest, honey, apricot jam, roasted rye, floral. Taste of malt sweetness, grapefruit zest, a touch of pine, grains, dragon fruit. Juicy.
beer_name: Forked River Riptide Rye Pale Ale

review_blob: 750ml bottle. Slightly hazy golden body, medium white head, average retention, no lacing. Aroma of yeast, grains, bananas, tart pears, coriander. Taste dominated by yeast and pears, bananas, coriander, grains, a touch of grass. Lively carbonated. Nicely done.

500ml bottle. Hazy golden body, big white dense head with good retention, almost no lacing. Aroma of herbs, cloves, banana, coriander, yeast, citruses. Taste of banana liquor, yeast, sugar, honey, a touch of herbs. Great sample.

500ml can. Clear pale yellow body, medium white head, average retention, plenty of lacing. Aroma of mineral water, metal can, grains, hay, grass. Clear taste: grains, herbs, mineral water, a touch of hops. A tad too sweet.
500ml bottle. Clear golden body, medium white head, poor retention and no lacing. Aroma of grains, coriander, sour notes, banana, yeast. Taste of wheat, banana, sugar. Meh.

473ml can. Clear golden body, big white head, average retention, plenty of lacing. Fresh aroma of pine, grapefruit, oranges, honey, grains. Taste of grapefruit zest, honey, resins, dragon fruit and peaches. Nice one.

650ml bottle. Clear cola body, small beige head with poor retention. Aroma of licorice, vanilla, roasted nuts, blackberry jam, hints of oak. Taste roasted malts, light smokiness, nuts, hints of bourbon, a touch of leather. Nice.
beer_name: Camerons Deviator Doppelbock - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: 650ml bottle. Dark brown body, small mocha head with average retention. Aroma condensed milk, milk chocolate, vanilla beans, gingerbread cookies, roasted malts. Taste of gingerbread cookies, milk chocolate, vanilla, well roasted malts. Lovely.
beer_name: Central City Red Racer Gingerhead Gingerbread Stout

review_blob: 330ml bottle. Slightly hazy golden body, big white head with average retention. Aroma of yeast, herbs, honey, peppercorn, pears and apples. Taste of honey, sugar, grains, herbs, yeast, apples in alcohol. A tad too sweet for my taste, but very nice.
